cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with time-encoded signals, which are commonly used in neuromorphic computing and social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses compression techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of Hawkes processes and entropy coding indicates that it could belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
